  "text": "The first-excited conformers of [2SU]Na + and [6Me2SU]Na + are higher in Gibbs free energy than the ground-state ones by 15.6 and 12.6 kJ/mol, respectively, and would not be expected to be present in the experiments [CITATION_1] . Based on these observations, one may assume that in the gas phase under our electrospray conditions, the ground-state conformer, 3, would be the solely existing precursor to the hydrated complexes, 3a and 3b.",
